### **Data Storage Strategy**

#### **Supabase Schema:**

sql  
*\-- Time-series financial/operational data*  
CREATE TABLE metric\_snapshots (  
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen\_random\_uuid(),  
  user\_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id),  
  period DATE NOT NULL, *\-- 2025-01-01 for Jan 2025*  
  metric\_category TEXT, *\-- 'financial', 'operational', 'team'*  
  metric\_name TEXT, *\-- 'revenue', 'team\_size', 'utilization'*  
  metric\_value NUMERIC,  
  metric\_unit TEXT, *\-- 'usd', 'percentage', 'count'*  
  source\_document TEXT, *\-- filename of upload*  
  upload\_id UUID, *\-- groups metrics from same upload*  
  created\_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()  
);

*\-- Upload tracking*  
CREATE TABLE uploads (  
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen\_random\_uuid(),  
  user\_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id),  
  document\_type TEXT, *\-- 'p\_and\_l', 'balance\_sheet', 'utilization'*  
  file\_name TEXT,  
  file\_url TEXT, *\-- Supabase storage URL*  
  period\_start DATE,  
  period\_end DATE,  
  extraction\_status TEXT, *\-- 'pending', 'complete', 'failed'*  
  created\_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()  
);  
\`\`\`

\*\*Why this structure:\*\*  
\- Each metric is a separate row (enables flexible querying)  
\- Time-series enabled (can query "revenue for last 12 months")  
\- Supports multi-category data (not just financial)  
\- Tracks source documents (user can see where data came from)

